<item>
            <title>[FLINK-24380] Flink should handle the state transition of the pod from Pending to Failed</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-24380</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In K8s, there is five phases in pod&apos;s lifecycle: Pending, Running, Secceeded, Failed and Unknown. Currently, Flink does not handle the state transition of the pod from Pending to Failed. If a pod failed from Pending by `OutOfCPU` or `OutOfMem`, it will never be released and Flink keep waiting for it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To fix this issue, Flink should terminate the pod in Failed phase proactively.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
